Class SourcePayloadBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mozilla.secops.parser.PayloadBase
      • com.mozilla.secops.parser.SourcePayloadBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AmoDocker, ApacheCombined, Auth0, BmoAudit, Cloudtrail, Duopull, FxaAuth, FxaContent, GcpAudit, GcpVpcFlow, GLB, IPrepdLog, Nginx, OpenSSH, Phabricator, Taskcluster

    public abstract class SourcePayloadBase
extends PayloadBase
implements Serializable
    Extension of PayloadBase that unifies source address field handling

    Payload types that manipulate some indication of a source address field should likely inherit from this class.

    See Also:

      • setSourceAddress

        public void setSourceAddress(String sourceAddress,
                             com.mozilla.secops.parser.ParserState state,
                             Normalized n)
        Set source address field

        If the state value is non-null, elements within the parser state such as an initialized GeoIP object will be used as part of geo-ip resolution.

        If n is non-null, the source address value will also be mirrored into the normalized event field.

        Parameters:
        sourceAddress - Source address
        state - Parser state
        n - Normalized field from base event
